label: uncl7075
comment: Code specifying a level of packaging.

values.label: Inner
values.comment: Level of packing, if it exists, that is immediately subordinate to the intermediate packaging level.

values.label: Intermediate
values.comment: Level of packaging, if it exists, that is immediately subordinate to the outer packaging level.

values.label: Outer
values.comment: For packed merchandise, outermost level of packaging for a shipment.

values.label: No packaging hierarchy
values.comment: There is no specifiable level of packaging: packaging is inner and outer level as well.

values.label: Shipment level
values.comment: The packaging level being described is the shipment level.

values.label: Highest
values.comment: Level of packaging, if it exists, which is highest in the packaging hierarchy.
